<header class="hero">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p class="lede">What the <code>eleventy</code> template demonstrates.</p>
</header>
<section class="card">
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Data files</strong> — <code>_data/site.json</code> and <code>_data/nav.json</code> drive the shell.</li>
    <li><strong>Collections</strong> — Markdown in <code>src/posts/</code> becomes the <code>posts</code> collection.</li>
    <li><strong>Pagination</strong> — the Posts page splits the collection into pages.</li>
    <li><strong>Filters</strong> — <code>readableDate</code>, <code>head</code>, and the universal <code>url</code> filter for base paths.</li>
    <li><strong>Shortcodes</strong> — <code>{% raw %}{% year %}{% endraw %}</code> and the paired <code>note</code> callout.</li>
    <li><strong>Theming</strong> — a persisted light/dark toggle and a GitHub source link in the top bar.</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="muted">Source: <a href="https://github.com/__REPO_SLUG__">github.com/__REPO_SLUG__</a></p>
</section>
